# TCG (The Cruise God) — Production Ready Roadmap

With the core demo goals 100% wired and functional, we are now moving to **Production-Grade Optimizations** to support mass adoption and professional deployment.

## Proposed Improvements

### 1. Persistence & Data Layer (Mass Adoption Friendly)
- **Database Integration**: Replace `localStorage` with a persistent database (Supabase / PostgreSQL). This allows users to access their Trophy Room across devices.
- **Trophy Sharing Links**: Generate unique, shareable URLs for every trophy moment with proper OpenGraph metadata for social previews (Discord, X, Instagram).

### 2. Performance & Scalability
- **Edge Runtime**: Move all API routes (`/api/search-*`) to the Next.js Edge Runtime to minimize global latency.
- **Result Caching**: Implement `Upstash Redis` to cache common search results (e.g., "best bars in Chicago") to reduce Firecrawl costs and improve speed.
- **Image Optimization**: Use Next.js [Image](file:///d:/backups%20to%20free%20space/TCG%28TheCruiseGod%29/app/src/app/lib/shareUtils.ts#22-41) component and specialized loaders for trophy screenshots.

### 3. Security & Reliability
- **Rate Limiting**: Add `Upstash Ratelimit` to protect against API abuse and cost spikes.
- **Sentry Integration**: Add error monitoring to catch client-side voice issues or API timeouts in real-time.
- **Authentication**: Prepare for `Supabase Auth` integration to allow verified user profiles. Supabase Auth perfectly pairs with our Supabase Postgres DB and Row Level Security (RLS) policies.

